<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>In
addition, crews above &#8220;green&#8221; have a limited ability to repair
damaged components on their ship.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>A=
lso, ships
that have a repair mission and manage to self-repair (through any means) wi=
ll
have their repair mission cancelled.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Fighter Aces</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: As with crews, fighters can gain experi=
ence
as well. When a pilot obtains his first experience perk he will get a custom
name.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Exploration ship and construction ship si=
ze</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: These two ships max size i=
s now
the same as an empire&#8217;s military ship max size. Previously they we not
modified by either military or civilian empire size factor.<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Bacon Civilian Shipyards</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: The game now uses the pira=
te ship
building interface so you can build all ship classes now. Need 50 freighter=
s?
Don&#8217;t wait for the private sector. Build them yourself. Note that the=
se
ships will be state ships and the state will pay their maintenance costs.<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Armed Civilian Ships</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Civilian ships can now hav=
e up to
10 weapons.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Order Passenger Ships</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: If you have a passenger sh=
ip
selected and press Ctrl-W the game will perform a passenger transport missi=
on
from SOURCE to DESTINATION as defined in passengers.txt. Be sure to only do
this for a passenger ship that doesn&#8217;t already have passengers otherw=
ise
the existing passengers may disappear into limbo. Not a lot of error checki=
ng
here so make sure you spell the planet name exactly correct (copy past from
within the game is best). Note: you can keep the passengers.txt file open. =
Just
save it after updating it and the new setting will take effect.<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>I=
f you hold
down SHIFT while assigning a mission to a state passenger ship the mission =
will
repeat until you clear it with the ship finder (!clear).<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Bacon Input (Ship Finder)</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Press control-E to bring u=
p a
search box. Type the name of any one of your ships or planets and the first
match will become the selected object. Good for when you have 500+ ships and
know the name but don&#8217;t feel like searching through the <span
class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> (even sorted the <span class=3DSpellE>shipli=
st</span>
can still be a chore).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>P=
lease
note, The <span class=3DSpellE>ShipFinder</span> has now been renamed
&#8220;Bacon Input&#8221; because it now does so much more. All special
commands (those starting <span class=3DGramE>with !</span> or #) are input
through this box.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

