<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Assign Cargo Mission</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Select a freighter and pre=
ss Alt-3
to order it to move resources from SOURCE to DESTINATION. SOURCE is set by
selecting the desired source and pressing Alt-1. DESTINATION is set with Al=
t-2.
Source and destination remain set until you change it or reload a saved gam=
e so
you can order several freighters on the same route quickly. Freighters will
pick up all resources that the source has in large quantity. If multiple
resources are present in the same amount then the freighter will split its
cargo hold evenly between them.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>I=
f you hold
down SHIFT while assigning a mission to a state freighter the mission will
repeat until you clear it with the ship finder (!clear).<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>I=
f the
mission target is a construction ship the freighter will try to fill up the
constructor&#8217;s holds evenly with each type of strategic resource.<o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>T=
o force a
manual cargo mission to carry just the resources you want you can use <span
class=3DGramE>the !cargos</span> command as follows:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span lang=3DE=
N-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!cargos, [cargo name], [cargo2 name], etc=
<o:p></o:p></span></i></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>E=
xample<span
class=3DGramE>: <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!cargos</i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>, Caslon, <span class=3DSpellE>Dilithi=
um</span>
Crystal</i> (Note, you must put a comma between each term including the word
cargos and the first assigned cargo.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>T=
o clear
the list just <span class=3DGramE>enter <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:nor=
mal'>!cargos</i></span>
with nothing after it.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Assign Mining Mission:</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'><span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Select a planet you wish to mine a=
nd
press <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>Alt-M</i>. The closest mining=
 ship
without a mission will move there to mine it. It will deliver the cargo to =
the
closes space station. If you press <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>=
Alt-Shift-A</i>
and you have a specific destination set (with <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-sty=
le:
normal'>Alt-2</i>) then it will deliver to that destination instead. As alw=
ays
you can order a ship to not unload with <span class=3DGramE>the <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=3DSpellE>nodump</span></i=
></span>
command. After giving this order the ordered ship will be selected.<o:p></o=
:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>More Ship Images</span></b><span lang=3DE=
N-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Each family of ships can have up to fou=
r more
images for each class of ship. <span class=3DGramE>So</span> you can have
&#8220;destroyer&#8221;, &#8220;destroyer1&#8221;, &#8230;
&#8220;destroyer4&#8221;.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Full Freighters</span></b><span lang=3DEN=
-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Freighters will always try to max out t=
heir
load if their destination is a base or planet. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Fighter Fun</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Fighters/Bombers can have longer range.=
 In
addition, fighters from bases will always have 1.4 times the range of other
fighters. Other fighter options included limited ammo, cost to build, build
time, and extra damage against bombers. See BaconSettings.txt for details.<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:=
normal'><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>HyperFun</span></b></span><s=
pan
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Hyperjump settings can be =
changed
from the BaconSettings.txt file. See file comments for details.<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Better Interface</span></b><span lang=3DE=
N-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Diplomacy screen has higher money amoun=
ts for
deals larger than 10,000 credits. Font and background <span class=3DSpellE>=
colors</span>
(drop shadow) changed on some screens for better readability.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>This is set with Shadow=3Dfalse in=
 the
config file.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>W=
hen
designing a ship, selecting an existing component will auto select the same
component on the left-hand list unless the selected component is obsolete. =
This
way you can easily add more of an existing component.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>I=
tems on
the diplomacy screen are now ordered alphabetically. Extra cash options abo=
ve
10,000 have been added if you have the cash available.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-a=
nsi-language:
EN-AU'>Shiplist</span></span><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:=
EN-AU'>
screen and fleet display in the info panel now have <span class=3DSpellE>co=
lor</span>
indicators to differentiate damage types. Yellow ships have only <span
class=3DSpellE>armor</span> damaged. Aqua ships have lost their hyperdrive.=
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Order multiple troops</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: With the desired planet se=
lect on
the colonies screen, bring up the ship finder and type <span class=3DGramE>=
&#8220;!troops</span>
X&#8221; to order up X number of troops. This will save a lot of clicking if
you build a lot of troops.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Ship Cycler</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: <span class=3DGramE>Alt ;</span> and <s=
pan
class=3DGramE>Alt &#8217;</span> to cycle backward/forward through all of y=
our
ships with the same <span class=3DSpellE>subrole</span> as the currently se=
lected
ship. If you have your view locked (&#8216;L&#8217; key) the view will chan=
ge
with each selection. (If Alt doesn&#8217;t work try Ctrl.)<o:p></o:p></span=
></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Cargo Mission Viewer</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: With a freighter with a ca=
rgo
mission selected, press <span class=3DSpellE><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-styl=
e:normal'>ctrl+enter</i></span>
to see its mission cargo order and its current cargo.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Damage Viewer</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: View a list of damaged components with
control-R.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Science Ships</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Automated exploration ships with labs w=
ill
pursue research projects independently. Each science ship will pick one
research project for each type of lab it has (Energy, high-tech, weapons). =
Each
month it will contribute research points toward that project until it if
learned. The amount if set in the settings file. After the first month you =
can
use the new Alt + Ctrl + right click menu to set the specific research proj=
ect
for the science ship.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Bomber Bays</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Fighter bays and bomber bays can now be
separate, allowing you to choose how many of each type your carriers carry.
This requires the <span class=3DSpellE>BaconWorld</span> components.txt,
research.txt and fighters.txt files. AI ships will keep the 50/50 split bet=
ween
fighters and bombers. The settings file allows you to specific a specific
string that the game will look for in each fighter bay component to determi=
ne
if that bay will produce fighters, bombers or an even split.<o:p></o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Stars and Galaxy Size</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Number of stars is no long=
er
limited by galaxy size. Previously a 4x4 galaxy had a limit of 400 stars. T=
he
star limit increased by one notch on the slider for each increase in the ga=
laxy
size. This limit has been removed. Also, a new size &#8220;Bacon Big&#8221;=
 has
been added with 2000 stars.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>A=
dditionally,
the lowest star setting value can be overwritten with the <span class=3DSpe=
llE>lowStarCount</span>
value in the settings file. Note that in order for this value to be used on=
 a
new game you have to start or load a game to get the settings to initialize=
 and
then go to the main screen and start your actual game.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Custom Start Screen</span></b><span lang=
=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: If your mod contains a file called
&#8220;customBackgroundImage.jpg&#8221; in the \Customization\[mod name]\im=
ages
folder, it will use that one instead of the regular DWU start screen. Please
note that the game title &#8220;Distant Worlds Universe&#8221; is actually =
on
the start screen so if you replace it with a custom start screen you should
probably include &#8220;Distant Worlds Universe&#8221; somewhere on the new
screen for legal reasons.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Integration with Bacon Stats Viewer</span=
></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: The game will dump two xml=
 files
&#8220;SaveStatsEmpires.xml&#8221; and &#8220;SaveStatsPirates.xml&#8221; t=
hat
will track game stats such as income, military strength, population, etc. T=
hese
files can be viewed in the Bacon stats viewer. The viewer can be left open =
and
just click the &#8216;refresh&#8217; button to get an update. Note that the=
se
two files have to be deleted when starting a new game or else you will still
have the old game stats and it will look ugly. The interval for dumping dat=
a is
configurable in the settings file. Default is 90 days.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Asteroid Colonies</span></b><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Colony ships can now create asteroid
colonies. The procedure is slightly different from a regular colonize missi=
on.
Order your colony ship to the asteroid and then use the new <span class=3DS=
pellE>alt+ctrl</span>+
right click menu and select the colonize option. This will create a 30,000
person colony on the asteroid and deduct the amount of credits configured in
the settings file.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Terraforming</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: The terraforming facility (#9 in
Facilities.txt) now has its second and third values used to raise a
planet&#8217;s habitability rating. Previously they were zero. The second v=
alue
is the rate of terraforming and the third value is the limit to which habit=
ability
can be raised. Default values are 500 and 80.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Hold Position</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Using the new Alt + Ctrl + Right Click =
menu a
ship can be told to hold position and will ignore all orders (from player or
AI) to do anything else until you cancel the hold order. This is useful to
prevent ships from flying off and attacking other threats in system, for
example.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Trade Everything</span></b><span lang=3DE=
N-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: If this option is enabled in the settin=
gs
file all known bases and planets will appear on the diplomacy trade screen.
This has been made optional because some people have reported the game taki=
ng
up to 15 minutes to load this screen when there are hundreds of bases in the
late game.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Also, bases attach=
ed to
a colony will not be tradable even if this option is enabled. It causes too
many weird situations since those bases share their cargo with the colony. =
Regardless
of the setting CTRL-T will add the currently selected base (or ship) to the
trade screen the next time it is opened. It is cleared after closing the tr=
ade
screen.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!note</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: This will add a reminder note to the
currently selected ship. When the ship completes its mission it will <span
class=3DSpellE>popup</span> the message and allow you to select the ship if
desired. Leave a space <span class=3DGramE>between !note</span> and your me=
ssage.
To clear a message just <span class=3DGramE>type !note</span> with no messa=
ge.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>War Weariness</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: In default Distant Worlds all war weari=
ness
is reset to zero when your last war ends. Instead, it will drop slowly over
time.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Weapon Range Circles</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>:<span class=3DGramE><span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>!<span class=3DSpellE>rangecircles=
</span></span>
toggles this on and off. With it on, the current selected ship will have
circles around it showing the range of its weapons.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Since enemy weapon range is displa=
yed in
vanilla DW, the range circles work for enemy ships as well.<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Reload Ship Templates</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; Normally ship templ=
ates for
AI empires are only loaded on game start (or when a new empire is created).=
 Now
you can make changes to the templates and have the game reload them to take
effect in your current game. The command for this <span class=3DGramE>is <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=3DSpellE>loadtemplates</s=
pan></i></span>.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DGramE><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:no=
rmal'><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>loadte=
mplates</span></span></i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-l=
anguage:
EN-AU'> <span class=3DGramE>true<span style=3D'font-style:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>will</span></span></span></i><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> include the player&#8217;s =
empire.
Otherwise it will only apply to AI empires. To use this command, go to the =
<span
class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> screen and select the classes of ships for w=
hich
you want the Ai to regenerate designs. Then use ctrl-e and enter the comman=
d.
Note that it will not obsolete your old designs so you might want to do that
first manually. Alao, it will pick new names for your new designs so you may
want to rename them afterward.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>No Independents</span></b><span lang=3DEN=
-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> <span class=3DGramE>-<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>A</span> new setting in the
Baconsettings.txt file allows you to override the <span class=3DSpellE>losw=
est</span>
setting of the &#8220;independent life slider bar&#8221; on galaxy creation.
The lowest setting corresponds to a value of 150. You can lower it as low a=
s 1
to get rid of independents. Do not set it to zero as it is used as a diviso=
r in
some places and will crash. You may still see some independents but they are
probably pirates. Also, if you try to load a saved game that used a differe=
nt
value you MAY get a failure to load. This has not been extensively tested a=
nd
should be considered experimental. Like the &#8220;low stars&#8221; setting=
, it
is not initialized until after a game starts so if you want to see the affe=
cts
you must either start or load a game and THEN go back to the main menu and
start your actual game.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Improved mining cap with tech increase</s=
pan></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; Value 2 (which is z=
ero in
vanilla DW) is now used to override the mining rate cap. In <span class=3DS=
pellE>unmodded</span>
DW the mining rate cap is 10 for mining and luxury mining and 40 for gas
mining. You can now change that with tech advanced. See the entries in
research.txt for suggested values. If you leave it as zeros then the default
values will be used (10, 10, 40).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Loans</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> <span class=3DGramE>-<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>You</span> can now get a loan when=
 you
need more cash. !loan [amount] will let you see how the terms of the loan a=
nd,
if you agree, you will take out the loan. <span class=3DGramE>Entering !loa=
n</span>
without an amount will show you any outstanding loans you currently have.<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Ransoming Captured Spies</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; There is now a chan=
ce that
a captured spy will be put in prison instead of killed. This is controlled =
in
the <span class=3DSpellE>BaconSettigns</span> with a value between 0.0 and =
1.0
where 1.0 means a captured spy will always be taken alive and put in prison.
Open the prisoner screen with Ctrl-P to view your prisoners as well as your
spies being held on other planets that are available to ransom back. When a=
 spy
is captured you won&#8217;t know right away if the AI will allow them to be
ransomed back. They will make that decision at some point in the future
(usually 45-180 days). Spies may also defect or escape. The chance of this =
is
configurable in the settings file.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Remove Background Stars</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: When zoomed out the backgr=
ound
stars are displayed using an image&#8221; images\environment\<span
class=3DSpellE>galaxybackdrops</span>\galaxy_backdrop.jpg&#8221;. Replacing=
 this
with a solid black image will remove the stars. When zoomed in the stars are
drawn programmatically. You can now set the level of zoom where the stars w=
ill
be drawn. Set <span class=3DSpellE>backgroundStarsAtZoomLevel</span>=3D0 in=
 the
BaconSettings.txt to remove background stars. <span class=3DSpellE>backgrou=
ndStarsAtZoomLevel</span>=3D300
is the default level.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>New <span class=3DSpellE>Shiplist</span> =
options</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: The <span class=3DSpellE>s=
hiplist</span>
screen has extra selection options: damaged ships, low fuel ships, etc. <o:=
p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>In
addition, if you have a ship or planet selected the <span class=3DSpellE>sh=
iplist</span>
will have a default sort order based on distance from the selected object. =
If
you have selected a column header and sorted your <span class=3DSpellE>ship=
list</span>
then the game will continue to use the sort order you selected. To unsort a=
 <span
class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> click the column with the empire flag. If no
object is selected the game will use the normal <span class=3DSpellE>shipli=
st</span>
<span class=3DSpellE>behavior</span>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Free Traders</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Using the <span class=3DGramE>command <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=3DSpellE>freetrader</span=
></i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'> X</i> turns a state-run freighter int=
o an
independent trader with X initial cash (taken as a loan from your state fun=
ds).
To pay off your loan, once you&#8217;ve earned some cash, <span class=3DGra=
mE>use
!<span class=3DSpellE>freetrader</span></span> with a negative value for X.=
 To
retire and return your freighter to general service, <span class=3DGramE>us=
e <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=3DSpellE>freetrader</span=
></i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'> 0</i>. To trade with a planet or base=
 use
the <span class=3DSpellE><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>alt+Ctrl+r=
ight</i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'> click</i> menu when you are within ra=
nge
300. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>S=
ome items
on the trade panel are <span class=3DSpellE>color</span> coded. Gold and si=
lver
are commodities which are higher priced than usual. Try to sell these. Light
green and red are commodities below market value. Try to buy these. <span
class=3DGramE>Use <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!price</i></span>=
 to help
you find a good place to buy or sell. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>F=
ree
traders pay for their own maintenance, not the state unless they are automa=
ted
and then the state pays the maintenance. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>F=
ree
traders can also collect resources and even ship components from ships they
defeat in battle. These ship components can be installed at any independent
planet or asteroid colony using the alt ctrl right click menu. <o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>F=
ree
traders can <span class=3DSpellE>aslo</span> recruit officers with the alt =
ctrl
right click menu. The cost is set in the BaconSettings.txt file. <o:p></o:p=
></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>N=
ote: the
free trader price system takes about a year to fully seed in a new game so =
it
is advised to wait a year before making a free trader.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Subjugation Tribute</span></b><span lang=
=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: The percent of income that subjugated e=
mpires
pay as tribute has been made modifiable. It is controlled by the setting <s=
pan
class=3DSpellE>SubjugationTributePercentage</span> in the BaconSettings.txt=
 file.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Longer range weapons on bases</span></b><=
span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: You can now configure base=
s to
have a weapon range longer than ships. The setting that controls this is in=
 the
BaconSettings.txt <span class=3DSpellE>weaponRangeMultiplierForBases</span>=
. It
is a multiple so 2 equals 200% normal range. Make bases great again.<o:p></=
o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Infrastructure:</span></b><span lang=3DEN=
-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> You can now add infrastructure improveme=
nts to
a colony with <span class=3DGramE>the <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:norma=
l'>!infrastructure</i></span>
command. This will raise the development level of the colony. Settings are
configurable in the BaconSettings.txt file. You can check how much of an ef=
fect
you are receiving by selecting the planet and pressing <span class=3DSpellE=
>Ctrtl</span>-Enter.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Zoom with mouse wheel when other menus are
open:</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> You c=
an now
use the mouse wheel to zoom even when other menus are open. If the menu is
focused on a control, such as a <span class=3DSpellE>listbox</span>, that s=
crolls
when using the mouse wheel, you will have to select something else before
zooming. Hold down right mouse button to drag the map.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Ship ETA to Waypoint:</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> Ships now show the estimate=
d time
until arrival at their next waypoint in seconds. This is only for individual
ships, not ships in fleets.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Pirate commission ships at Independent
colonies:</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> P=
irates
can now commission construction ships to be built at independent colonies t=
hey
control. Select the planet and use the alt-Ctrl-right click menu.<o:p></o:p=
></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Repair and refit only bases: </span></b><=
span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Bases whose name begins with=
 -- will
only repair and refit ships but not initiate new construction. This can help
you manage where new ships will be built and avoid long delays caused from
building at bases low on resources.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Ship targeting restrictions:</span></b><s=
pan
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> A ship (or fleet) can be gi=
ven a
targeting restriction to avoid targeting certain types of targets. The comm=
and <span
class=3DGramE>is <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=3DSpe=
llE>notarget</span></i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'> [type]</i> where type can be any of:<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l=
