</span></span></span><![endif]><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-languag=
e:EN-AU'>Faster<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>E=
nter with
no parameter to clear the setting. While the setting can be given to a fleet
that just passes the setting to each ship in the fleet. There is no setting=
 for
the fleet so if you add ships to the fleet later you should reissue the
setting. You can check a ship&#8217;s setting with <i style=3D'mso-bidi-fon=
t-style:
normal'>Ctrl-Enter</i>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:=
normal'><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>PointDefense</span></b></spa=
n><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-=
language:
EN-AU'> and Missiles:</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-langua=
ge:EN-AU'>
With this option set to true in the settings file point <span class=3DSpell=
E>defense</span>
and beam weapons can intercept missiles. The point <span class=3DSpellE>def=
ense</span>
weapons will fire their animation but the beam weapons won&#8217;t. Instead=
 I
added a small animation to show the missile has been shot down. The
interception isn&#8217;t 100% and there is a myopic zone if you get too clo=
se.
Also there is a bug that sometimes allows missiles to insta-hit their target
regardless of point <span class=3DSpellE>defense</span>. It&#8217;s <span
class=3DSpellE>kinda</span> rare. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Split off a planet to from a new Empire:<=
/span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> The <span class=3DGramE>com=
mand <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=3DSpellE>splitoff</span><=
/i></span>
can be used to give independence to a planet in your empire that you
don&#8217;t want anymore. The newly formed empire will start with a positive
relationship bonus due to being granted independence. Alternatively, you can
add &#8220;false&#8221; and the newly formed empire will start as a subjuga=
ted
one instead. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Pirate Respawn commands:</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> The <span class=3DGramE>com=
mand <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=3DSpellE>piraterespawn</s=
pan></i></span>
will toggle the game setting allowing or forbidding the creation of new pir=
ate
empires during the game. You can also <span class=3DSpellE>used</span> the =
<span
class=3DGramE>command <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=
=3DSpellE>respawnpiratesnow</span></i></span>
to generate new pirates immediately if the current number of pirates is bel=
ow
the number specified in the game setup.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Invasion Strategy:</span></b><span lang=
=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> This is a little subgame you can play wh=
en
invading a planet to try and guess the opposing side&#8217;s strategy. If y=
ou
are successful your troops will receive a bonus. If not, they will be
penalized. Settings are controlled in the BaconSettings.txt file. Access wi=
th
the <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>alt-ctrl-right click </i>menu o=
n the
target planet with the planet selected. If you quit after taking a turn it
counts as a loss.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

